dct_description_sm: "Topography by A.W. Chase and E.F. Dickins, Asistants, between 1868 and 1887. Hydrography by A.W. Chase, Asistant in 1868. The bar is from an examination by the Corps of Engineers U.S.A in 1894. Astronomical and magnetic observations by F. Morse, Sub-Assistant and R.A Marr, assistant in ... 1885 and 1888."
"Published August 1895. W.W. Duffield, Superintendent; verified O.H. Tittman, Assistant in Charge of the Office. J.F. Moser, Lieut. Comdr. U. SN. Hydrographic Inspector."
Relief shown by contours and spot heights. Depths shown by soundings and isolines.
